data.content:
The `Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi` 10.0 package upgraded from **OpenAPI.NET v1 to v2**, which restructured the object model significantly. Here are the breaking changes in your code:

## 1. `OpenApiAny` types removed
`OpenApiString`, `OpenApiInteger`, etc. are gone. Use `JsonNode` instead:

```csharp
// Before
param.Schema.Example = new OpenApiString("1.0");

// After
param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
```

Add `using System.Text.Json.Nodes;`

## 2. `OpenApiResponse` → responses are now keyed differently
`operation.Responses` is now `IDictionary<string, OpenApiResponse>` but the constructor changed:

```csharp
// Still works, but ensure you're using the new namespace if needed
operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });
```

This one likely still compiles — verify your `using` statements.

## 3. `OpenApiReference` collapsed into the scheme itself
`Reference` and `Type`/`ReferenceType` changed. References are now just a `string` identifier:

```csharp
// Before
var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecurityScheme
{
    Reference = new OpenApiReference { Type = ReferenceType.SecurityScheme, Id = "oauth2" }
};
operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
{
    new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes }
};

// After
var schemeRef = new OpenApiSecurityScheme { Reference = new OpenApiReference("oauth2") };
operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
{
    new() { [schemeRef] = scopes }
};
```

`OpenApiReference` now takes the `id` directly in its constructor; the `Type` is inferred from context.

## 4. `Schema.Nullable` removed
OpenAPI v3.1 (which v2 of the library targets) uses JSON Schema's `type` array instead of `nullable`:

```csharp
// Before
property.Value.Nullable = false;

// After — nullable is expressed via the Type flags
property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null; // remove null from type union
```

Add `using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;` (for `JsonSchemaType`).

## Summary of required changes

| Issue | Fix |
|-------|-----|
| `new OpenApiString(...)` | `JsonValue.Create(...)` |
| `OpenApiReference { Type = ..., Id = ... }` | `new OpenApiReference("oauth2")` |
| `schema.Nullable = false` | `schema.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null` |
| `using Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` | Remove (no longer needed) |
| — | Add `using System.Text.Json.Nodes` |
